  "critical": true,
  "critical_note": "Without soil fertility management, crop yields decline 2-5% per year as nutrients are depleted, eventually making agriculture unsustainable",
  "description": "Systematic management of soil fertility through composting, cover cropping, and organic matter amendment. Composting converts animal manure, crop residues, and food waste into stable humus at 55-65°C, killing pathogens and weed seeds. Sustained crop yields depend on replacing nutrients removed by harvest.",
  "early_win": true,
  "early_win_note": "Composting animal manure and crop waste produces safe, stable fertilizer within 3-6 months, immediately improving crop yields 15-25%.",
